<p>What is the easiest way in c#/wpf to show user controls in a window depending on the viewmodel which is binded? Let's assume i have the following view models:</p>  <pre><code>public interface ISomeInterface {     string Name { get; set; } }  public class A : ISomeInterface {     public string Name { get; set; }     public string Size { get; set; }     public string Age { get; set; } }  public class B : ISomeInterface {     public string Name { get; set; }     public string Address { get; set; }     public string Job { get; set; } } </code></pre>  <p>Now i want to have some controls on the UI, which always exists (those from the interface) and some which depends on the bindene models (<code>A</code> and <code>B</code>).</p>  <p>What is the easiest way to decides in xaml, whether to show controls for model <code>A</code> or for model <code>B</code>?</p>  <p>Or is this bad practice?</p>  <p>Thank you!</p>